      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Guard sessions tail against dirty session store entries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFix `openclaw sessions tail` crashing when `sessions.json` contains dirty persisted entries without a usable `sessionId` or `sessionFile`.\n\nThis change normalizes persisted session-store string fields before using them and skips invalid entries instead of calling `.trim()` on undefined values.\n\n## What changed\n\n- add a shared normalizer for persisted `sessionFile` / `sessionId` values\n- update session transcript path resolution to ignore blank or non-string persisted fields\n- add a regression test covering a dirty cron store entry without a usable `sessionId`\n\n## Why\n\nA malformed session-store record could make `sessions tail` fail with:\n\n```text\nCannot read properties of undefined (reading 'trim')\n```\n\nWith this fix, the command continues working and only ignores the bad entry.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `openclaw sessions tail`\n- `openclaw sessions tail --tail 5`\n- `openclaw sessions tail --session-key main --tail 3`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/session-files.test.ts`",
        "branch": "fix/agent-select-sync",
